Sime, Malaysian Planters Slump After Palm Oil Prices Decline

-- B y   C h a n   T i e n   H i n
-- 
2011-10-03T02:40:26Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-03/sime-malaysian-planters-slump-after-palm-oil-prices-decline.html
Sime Darby Bhd. (SIME)  fell the most in two
weeks in Kuala Lumpur trading, leading a slump in Malaysian
plantation stocks after palm oil prices slid.  Sime lost 4 percent to 8.10 ringgit at 10:34 a.m. local
time, set for its steepest drop since Sept. 15.  Kuala Lumpur
Kepong Bhd. (KLK)  lost 3.9 percent to 20.28 ringgit and IOI Corp.
declined 3.4 percent to 4.49 ringgit. Palm oil dropped as much
as 2.7 percent to 2,827 ringgit per metric ton.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Chan Tien Hin at 
 thchan@bloomberg.net  